&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct option 1) &lt;/strong&gt;The error lies in &lt;strong&gt;part A.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/09/428%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 48px; height: 48px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Explanation:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Here, it should be &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;acting up&amp;rsquo; &lt;/strong&gt;instead of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;acting down&amp;rsquo; &lt;/strong&gt;in the first part.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;Act&amp;nbsp;up&amp;rsquo; &lt;/strong&gt;is a phrasal verb which means to act&lt;strong&gt; in a way different from that which is normal or expected, to misbehave, cause trouble.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Phrasal verbs:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;a verb that is made up of&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Main Verb&lt;/strong&gt; together with an&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;adverb&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;or a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;preposition&lt;/strong&gt;, or &lt;strong&gt;both.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; role=&quot;presentation&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Some other&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;phrasal verbs&lt;/strong&gt; of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;act&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​​​Act out &lt;/strong&gt;- to represent an action&amp;nbsp;(like performing a scene from a play), to express something such as a fantasy, to express one&amp;#39;s feeling through disruptive actions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Act on/upon -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;to use (something, such as a feeling or suggestion) as a reason or basis for doing something&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Act up to&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to fulfil in action, equal in action&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Act on - &lt;/strong&gt;to affect something, or to take action against something&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct sentence will be - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;On our trip to Neer Garh waterfall, my younger brother started &lt;strong&gt;acting up&lt;/strong&gt; because our parents decided for us to walk the rest of the journey, which was roughly four kilometres long, instead of renting a car.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
